<subSubSection id="C30663EAFFBA6C6BFCCB43D5A46EF830" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1320" pageId="12" pageNumber="1319" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFBA6C6AFCCB43D5A271F8D1" blockId="12.[811,1458,1778,2028]" box="[813,1026,1778,1804]" pageId="12" pageNumber="1319">SHELL DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFBA6C6BFCCB4235A7D0F957" blockId="12.[811,1458,1778,2028]" lastBlockId="13.[132,775,1618,1677]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="1320" pageId="12" pageNumber="1319">Small-sized shells with spire whorls of relatively medium height and robust outline. Spire whorls straight to coeloconoid, conical, with scalariform, slightly elevated spire whorls and angulated shoulders. Usual, faint spiral cords on early spire whorls, but no tubercles or beads. Subsutural flexure moderately deep, strongly curved, moderately asymmetrical. Maximum diameter on shoulder. Last whorl straight, conical. Aperture straight. Fasciole indistinct. Spiral grooves on the anterior part of last whorl.</paragraph>
<caption id="DF6360E9FFBB6C6BFF6240E0A356F9DE" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5764727" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5764727" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5764727/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" startId="13.[132,143,1479,1496]" targetBox="[132,1455,215,1438]" targetPageId="13">
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFBB6C6BFF6240E0A356F9DE" blockId="13.[132,1457,1479,1541]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">
FIG. 9. — 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFBB6C6BFF3340E0A788FA03" authority="(Brocchi, 1814)" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Brocchi" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[213,507,1479,1496]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conilithes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFF3340E0A704FA03" box="[213,375,1479,1496]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Conilithes striatulus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4D90FFBB6C6BFE6440E0A784FA03" author="BROCCHI G." box="[386,503,1479,1496]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref17383" refString="BROCCHI G. 1814. - Conchiologia fossile subapennina, con osservazioni geologiche sugli Apennini e sul suolo adiacente. Stamperia Reale, Milano, 1 - 2, 712 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11569" type="book chapter" year="1814">Brocchi, 1814</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
from Tortonian of Crete (Greece). Specimens shown in apertural, abapertural, and apical views under natural and UV light: 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFF3740FAA6ADFA35" bold="true" box="[209,222,1501,1518]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">A</emphasis>
, AMPG(IV) 2640, Panassos; 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFE2840FAA7A8FA35" bold="true" box="[462,475,1501,1518]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">B</emphasis>
, AMPG(IV) 2641, Panassos; 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFD2A40FAA4A9FA35" bold="true" box="[716,730,1501,1518]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">C</emphasis>
, MNHN.F.A72597, Crete; 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFC5340FAA5B0FA35" bold="true" box="[949,963,1501,1518]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">D</emphasis>
, MNHN.F.A72601, Psalidha; 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFB5E40FAA2B7FA35" bold="true" box="[1208,1220,1501,1518]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">E</emphasis>
, AMPG(IV) 2643, Panassos; 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFF6240D3A6FCF9DE" bold="true" box="[132,143,1524,1541]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">F</emphasis>
, AMPG(IV) 2639, Panassos; 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFE9940D3A7FEF9DE" bold="true" box="[383,397,1524,1541]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">G</emphasis>
, MNHN.F.A72600, Crete; 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFD8E40D3A405F9DE" bold="true" box="[616,630,1524,1541]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">H</emphasis>
, specimen MNHN.F.A72599, Crete; 
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFC4040D3A5DFF9DE" bold="true" box="[934,940,1524,1541]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">I</emphasis>
, AMPG(IV) 2642, Panassos. Scale bar: 1 cm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFBB6C6BFF624397A46EF830" blockId="13.[131,777,1712,2027]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">
COLOUR PATTERN VARIATION. — The colour pattern consists of fluorescent flammulae on the spire (
<figureCitation id="13272CE4FFBB6C6BFE3943EDA450F939" box="[479,547,1738,1762]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="14.[813,824,921,938]" captionTargetBox="[813,1456,215,880]" captionTargetId="figure-718@14.[813,1456,215,880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIG. 10. — Elements constituting the colour pattern of Conilithes striatulus (Brocchi, 1814), AMPG(IV) 2640, Panassos, Crete, Greece. Same specimen as in the Fig. 9A. Scale bar: 0.2 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5764729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5764729/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). The last whorl bears a primary pattern of irregular, fluorescent blotches. The blotches can be axial flammulae that continue from the spire whorls, towards the anterior of the shell, or can be spirally arranged as bands, parallel to a second pattern of fluorescent spiral lines of dots and dashes, along the length of the shell. The spiral rows of dots or dashes start at carina and continue along the length of shell. All patterns are occasionally disrupted by non-fluorescent blotches (
<figureCitation id="13272CE4FFBB6C6BFD6F42A4A4BCF847" box="[649,719,1923,1948]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="14.[813,824,921,938]" captionTargetBox="[813,1456,215,880]" captionTargetId="figure-718@14.[813,1456,215,880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIG. 10. — Elements constituting the colour pattern of Conilithes striatulus (Brocchi, 1814), AMPG(IV) 2640, Panassos, Crete, Greece. Same specimen as in the Fig. 9A. Scale bar: 0.2 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5764729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5764729/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). On some shells, a non-fluorescent band exists along the centre of the length of the shell, decorated with fluorescent spiral lines of dots or dashes (
<figureCitation id="13272CE4FFBB6C6BFF0A42F4A742F830" box="[236,305,2003,2027]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="14.[813,824,921,938]" captionTargetBox="[813,1456,215,880]" captionTargetId="figure-718@14.[813,1456,215,880]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIG. 10. — Elements constituting the colour pattern of Conilithes striatulus (Brocchi, 1814), AMPG(IV) 2640, Panassos, Crete, Greece. Same specimen as in the Fig. 9A. Scale bar: 0.2 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5764729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5764729/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
, non-fluorescent band).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30663EAFFBB6C6BFCCB4374A36BF830" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFBB6C6BFCCB4374A5E2F9B0" blockId="13.[811,1456,1619,2028]" box="[813,913,1619,1645]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA33061FFBB6C6BFCCB4355A36BF830" blockId="13.[811,1456,1619,2028]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">
This species has been reported from the Miocene (Burdigalian and Tortonian) and the Pliocene of 
<collectingCountry id="F30B70F1FFBB6C6BFAA343B5A30AF977" box="[1349,1401,1682,1708]" name="Italy" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Italy</collectingCountry>
(see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4D90FFBB6C6BFCCB4395A5BBF917" author="BROCCHI G." box="[813,968,1714,1740]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref17383" refString="BROCCHI G. 1814. - Conchiologia fossile subapennina, con osservazioni geologiche sugli Apennini e sul suolo adiacente. Stamperia Reale, Milano, 1 - 2, 712 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11569" type="book chapter" year="1814">Brocchi 1814</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 3, fig. 4; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4D90FFBB6C6BFB894395A28FF917" author="SACCO F." box="[1135,1276,1714,1740]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" pagination="1 - 54" refId="ref20961" refString="SACCO F. 1893 a. - I molluschi dei terreni terziarii del Piemonte e della Liguria. Parte 13 [a]: (Conidae) (Fasciolo Primo). Memorie della Reale Accademia delle Scienze di Torino, series 2, 44: 1 - 54." type="journal article" year="1893">Sacco 1893a</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 9, fig. 30). The Greek material (
<tableCitation id="C69E05DAFFBB6C6BFBFF43F5A21FF937" box="[1049,1132,1746,1772]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="12.[132,143,840,857]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,743]" captionTargetId="figure-514@12.[132,1455,215,743]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="TABLE 4. — Shell measurements and ratios Conilithes striatulus (Brocchi, 1814) from the Tortonian of Crete (Greece). Mean and standard deviation are computed from 11 complete specimens. The largest comes from Panassos (AMPG(IV) 2640)." pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Table 4</tableCitation>
) is very similar to the 
<typeStatus id="54A78EC3FFBB6C6BFA9743F5A52FF8D7" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFBB6C6BFC6343D5A243F8D7" authorityName="Brocchi" authorityYear="1814" box="[901,1072,1778,1804]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFC6343D5A243F8D7" box="[901,1072,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Conus striatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MSNM i4672) coming from the Pliocene. Unfortunately, no colour pattern under UV light is visible on the 
<typeStatus id="54A78EC3FFBB6C6BFC5A4216A26EF890" box="[956,1053,1841,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">lectotype</typeStatus>
(Giorgio Teruzzi, personal communication). Nevertheless, we do not observe any shell differences between the Greek specimens and the 
<typeStatus id="54A78EC3FFBB6C6BFB294256A347F850" box="[1231,1332,1905,1931]" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">lectotype</typeStatus>
. Therefore, we consider them to belong to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFBB6C6BFB9342B6A331F870" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Brocchi" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[1141,1346,1937,1963]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conilithes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFB9342B6A331F870" box="[1141,1346,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Conilithes striatulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species slightly differs from the other 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFBB6C6BFB744296A339F810" box="[1170,1354,1969,1995]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conilithes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFBB6C6BFB744296A289F810" box="[1170,1274,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="1320">Conilithes</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by its the shorter spire whorls and its more robust shell.
</paragraph>
